posts.title: Brothers in Arms
posts.content:
I watched the final adventure of The Grand Tour last night. For those unfamiliar, the show is the continuance of the BBC Top Gear series that is hosted by Jeremy Clarkson, Richard Hammond, and James May. While the show is intended to be about cars it's really about the chemistry of 3 brothers from different mothers who have shared a bond and relationship for over 20 years.

Everyone who has participated on Patriots.win and /TheDonald on Reddit has shared a similar bond and adventure. While we may not have fought to keep some homebuilt automotive abomination on a Bolivian mountain road, we've fought meme wars together, registered voters together, and driven people to polls together to elect Donald J. Trump to the highest office.

Most of us will never meet each other in life.

We've shared hundreds, possibly thousands of hours together, which in some cases is more time together than we now spend with the family that raised us. There are things we discuss, rage, argue, laugh about that many outside this place will never understand. It can be bittersweet if you reflect on it for too long.

I don't know you, but I consider you a brother if you're here to Make America Great Again. I want to fight side by side with someone who shares this goal. I will forever be proud to fight this fight with you, and damn sure want to be here for the sharing of the salt.

We may not yet all comprehend this, but these times before November 5th are magical times that we won't get back. You see people refer to this place during 2016 and how magical it was. It was magical because we all made it magical. Magic is nostalgia, you're making it right now. Make it count.

While I may never meet you, I want you and your loved ones to pursue happiness in a restored country for as long as we are here on earth. While nothing is guaranteed in life I wish for you the freedom and autonomy to pursue your dreams, make mistakes, share your time with loved ones, know God, and ultimately grow old looking out across America the Beautiful.

The final episode of the Grand Tour featured the Dire Straits' song "Brothers in Arms" playing as they drove their last adventure together heading to a dried lake bed in Botswana. It was touching piece of music, and even it hits you even more when you learn that it was written for the soldiers that fought in the Falkland's war. While our war may only be a meme and ballot box war we are brothers in arms. God bless you my brothers!

"Brothers In Arms"

These mist covered mountains

Are a home now for me

But my home is the lowlands

And always will be

Some day you'll return to

Your valleys and your farms

And you'll no longer burn

To be brothers in arms

Through these fields of destruction

Baptisms of fire

I've witnessed your suffering

As the battle raged high

And though they did hurt me so bad

In the fear and alarm

You did not desert me

My brothers in arms

There's so many different worlds

So many different suns

And we have just one world

But we live in different ones

Now the sun's gone to hell

And the moon riding high

Let me bid you farewell

Every man has to die

But it's written in the starlight

And every line in your palm

We're fools to make war

On our brothers in arms
